撘字的基本解释

撘
dā
古同“搭”。

撘字的汉语字典释义

[①]［dā］
［《集韻》德合切，入合，端。］
亦作“撘1”。
(1)击，打。
(2)挂；披；戴。
(3)乘；坐。
(4)连接；接触。
(5)引申为勾搭。
(6)附上；依附。
(7)搭配。
(8)指连带；贴赔。
(9)支；架，架设。
(10)置放；安放。
(11)钩；扣上。
(12)扶，倚；按。
(13)量词。犹块，处，叠。
(14)附在指代词“这”、“那”等后面，表示处所。
(15)方言。介词。表示对象，相当于“與”、“給”。
(16)用同“褡”。短衫。
(17)姓。明有搭思。见《续通志·氏族八》。
[②]［tà］
［《廣韻》吐盍切，入盍，透。］
(1)同“搨”。描摹，仿制。
(2)往下按压。
(3)倒塌。

撘字的康熙字典解释

【卯集中】【手字部】　撘； 康熙笔画：16； 页码：页454第21
【唐韻】都合切。同搭。見搭字註。

Chinese dictionary definition of words
[①]［dā］
["Jiyun" is a combination of morality, integration, and end. ]
Also known as "撘1".
(1) Hit, hit.
(2) Hang; drape; wear.
(3) Multiply; sit.
(4) Connection; contact.
(5) The extension is hookup.
(6) Attached; attached.
(7) Collocation.
(8) Refers to joint and several; pay compensation.
(9) Support; frame, erection.
(10) Placement; Placement.
(11) Hook; buckle up.
(12) Support, lean; press.
(13) Quantifiers. You block, place, stack.
(14) Attached to the pronouns "this", "那", etc., to indicate the location.
(15) Dialects. preposition. Represents the object, which is equivalent to "and" and "given".
(16) Use the same as "褡". Short shirt.
(17) Last name. Obviously think about it. See "Continued History · Clan Eight".
[②]［tà］
["Guangyun" cuts into the spit, enters the spit, and penetrates. ]
(1) Same as "top". Tracing, imitation.
(2) Press down.
(3) Collapse.
